- "Chart the voyage of months" refers to tracking the progress over months;
- "Shiploads of assemblies launching" metaphorically represents the total number of assemblies created in each month;
- "Stormy waves of issues rising" symbolically indicates the total number of issues created each month;
- "Maritime timeline" symbolizes the chronological sequence of months tracked in the query.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS NumDirectories
FROM directories
WHERE directory_name LIKE 'A%';

SELECT a.assembly_id
  FROM assemblies a
  WHERE a.assembly_id NOT IN (
    SELECT i.assembly_id FROM issues i
  )
  AND a.directory_id IN (
    SELECT d.directory_id FROM directories d
    WHERE d.updated_at > datetime('now', '-30 days')
  );
